[ProMED thanks Kate Kelley for sending in a similar report.
This ongoing outbreak illustrates that almost all cases of
listeriosis are foodborne and appropriate genetic testing of isolates
on a large-scale basis will show relatedness of geographically
separated infections. Additionally, since listeriosis primarily
occurs in the elderly and in cellularly immunoincompetent people as
well as in pregnant women, the serving of high risk foods in
hospitals and homes for the elderly should be eliminated. As an
example, there is no reason to feed deli cold cuts as a lunch to a
hospitalized patient under treatment for lymphoma. - Mod.LL]
